    "long_instructions": "### Beats with Rests\r\n\r\nYou're going to create a backing track with pauses to make room for live coding improvisation Here's how:\r\n\r\n- One beat will play consistently throughout the entire backing track\r\n- Bass and lead tracks will be layered in at different times using rests\r\n\r\n**Here's what each sound should do:**\r\n\r\n- **Beat:** play a single beat that loops the entire time.\r\n- **Lead #1:** Play a lead twice, then rest for two measures. Repeat this sequence in a loop.\r\n- **Bass:** Rest for two measures, then play a bass track. Repeat this sequence in a loop.\r\n- **Lead #2:** Rest for 4 measures, then play a lead track. Repeat this in a loop.\r\n- All of these should play together!\r\n- Make sure the total loop lasts at least 24 measures!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/0f46228d84e8c103629bed310c4b2e3b-image-1745273944219.png)\r\n\r\nUse Live Coding to change the tracks that aren't playing so when the cycle restarts, it sounds different!",
